About Me

Hello! I am a hacker by passion, dedicated to uncovering weaknesses in systems and understanding how technology can be both a shield and a sword. My journey started with curiosity about how things work, and it has grown into a deep dive into cybersecurity and ethical hacking.

My work involves simulating black-hat techniques to help organizations secure their infrastructures. From reverse engineering to network infiltration, I specialize in techniques that reveal the vulnerabilities malicious hackers might exploit.

Outside of hacking, I am also a developer, innovator, and a lifelong learner eager to stay ahead of the evolving tech landscape.
